text:
*Position: (Junior) Research Engineer (fulltime), Skoltech, Moscow,  Statistical Machine Learning Group*
*Software engineers interested in Machine Learning and its applications are encouraged to apply.*

StatML lab focuses on research in modern statistics and machine learning with particular emphasis on probabilistically inspired approaches. We care about uncertainty a lot and try to ensure that the algorithms developed not only predict the outcome but also provide error bars for the predictions. The current research areas include Deep Learning and network analysis among several others. We aim to publish (and already do) at top-level conferences and journals in machine learning. Also, we conduct on-demand research for leading companies and institutions.
The group leader is Dr. Maxim Panov.

Samples of our recent research:
* <https://arxiv.org/abs/2003.03274>
* <https://arxiv.org/abs/2002.12253>
* <https://arxiv.org/pdf/2001.11411.pdf> (The Web Conference 2020)
* <https://arxiv.org/pdf/1904.06151.pdf> (ACML 2019)
* <https://arxiv.org/pdf/1902.10350.pdf> (IJCAI 2019)

*Job duties/responsibilities:*
-- Implement software development projects of the lab (development, testing, version control, etc.)
-- Automate and run machine learning experiments
-- Implement machine learning algorithms
-- Help with data acquisition and preprocessing

An ideal candidate is a person with experience in software development who wants to immerse in modern machine learning (for junior candidates) or possessing significant experience in ML.

*Conditions:*
-- Competitive salary (100 - 180K Rub gross)
-- Nice office, Skolkovo Innovation Center, Moscow (!!!<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wreSxwZW60c>)
-- Flexible work hours
-- Free medical insurance/gym

*Requirements:*
-- Experience with software processes and workflow
-- Good knowledge of Python
-- Good spoken and written English
-- MS or BA degree in math/CS/physics/engineering or a related field

*Great if you have experience with some of:*
-- Profiling/low-level optimizations of a code, CUDA
-- Open Source contributions
-- Experience with deep networks
-- Spark/Hadoop
-- implementing and evaluating ML algorithms
-- Publishing/contributing to good research papers (in English)

Please apply by sending CV to <mailto:m.panov@skoltech.ru|m.panov@skoltech.ru>, or altrav@Telegram

text:
*Vacancy: Data Scientist*
*Company: <http://Carnext.com|Carnext.com>*
*Location: Amsterdam, NL. Visa support is possible if you can reach Amsterdam.* 
Data and Analytics team of <http://CarNext.com|CarNext.com> is looking for Data Scientists! You are responsible for developing, testing, and maintaining Advanced Analytics algorithms and implementing them into applications. 
<http://CarNext.com|CarNext.com> is a pan-European digital scale-up marketplace for vehicles. In the Data and Analytics team, we maximize value creation with price setting and channel steering x2B, x2C. 
*Your responsibilities:*
Jointly develop hypotheses with the business, identify key patterns in data and communicate complex data insights as relevant business recommendations.
Develop, test, deploy and maintain predictive Advanced Analytical algorithms;
Create and maintain performance monitoring on predictive algorithms
Ensure scalability and flexibility of algorithms to be able to scale-up fast to a pan-European grid of predictive models.
Implement data-driven insights in day-to-day operations, and implement Advanced Analytical models to increase business value creation
Coach local country pricing experts on how to improve pricing and channel selection using data-driven tooling and information (~10 users across ~5 countries)
Coach and train junior Data Scientists on Data Science best practices (>2 at any point in time)
Quality control of Advanced Analytics algorithms
*Education:*
Academic degree (MSC) in Econometrics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence or another relevant quantitative field
*Your skills:*
4+ years of working experience in a commercial environment as a Data Scientist
4+ years of experience in Python - and advanced programming skills in other relevant languages like SQL, R
Relevant experience in a modern Cloud stack, e.g. AWS Redshift, S3. Some cloud experience is the must.
Proven track record of changing business processes with analytics (i.e., not only dashboarding)
Advanced knowledge of analytical and statistical techniques
Flourishes in a dynamic environment and able to cope with rapid change and demanding business requirements
Fluent in English, verbally and written
*Compensation:*
Salary 55-75k Euro gross + benefits:
13th salary, 8% holiday allowance, excellent pension plan, bonuses.
Application on <https://corporate.carnext.com/careers/vacancies/4688635002> 
If you have any questions feel free to reach me out:  <mailto:Andrey.zhelezniakov@carnext.com|Andrey.zhelezniakov@carnext.com>  
Or <https://www.linkedin.com/in/azhelezniakov/>
